git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"
Step 3: Set Default Branch Name (Optional)
git config --global init.defaultBranch main
Step 4: Verify Git Config
git config --list
🌐 Working with Remote Repositories
📥 Clone a Remote Repository
git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git
🔗 Add a Remote to an Existing Local Repo
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repository.git
⬆️ Push Changes to Remote
git add .
git commit -m "Your message here"
git push origin main
⬇️ Pull Changes from Remote
git pull origin main
📝 Replace:

"Your Name" with your name

"your.email@example.com" with your email

"origin" with your remote name (usually origin)

"main" with your branch name (e.g., main, master, etc.)
